{"word":"κλέω","slug":"κλέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, epic 2nd sg. <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>ἔκλεο</el> (for <el>ἐκλέεο</el>)\n<p/><i>to tell of, celebrate</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be famous</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>; <el>ἔνθ' ἀγοραὶ κλέονται</el> where <i>are held the famous</i> meetings, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}